div.p:
Japan and China, being equally animated by a sincere desire to settle amicably and in accordance with their common interest outstanding
questions relative to Shantung, have resolved to conclude a treaty for the settlement of such questions, and have to that end named as their Plenipotentiaries, that is to say:
His Majesty the Emperor of Japan:
Baron Tomosaburo Kato, Minister of the Navy;
Baron Kijuro Shidehara, Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary; and
Masanao Hanihara, Vice-Minister for Foreign Affairs;
His Excellency the President of the Chinese Republic:
Sao-Ke Alfred Sze, Envoy Extraordinary and Minister Plenipotentiary;
Vi Kyuin Wellington Koo, Envoy Extraordinary and Minister Plenipotentiary; and
Chung-Hui Wang, Former Minister of Justice;
